It won't win any awards for decor or food quality, but if it's a no-nonsense breakfast you're after, the Copper Top will fit the bill just fine.
Met a group of co-workers here for breakfast today; it was our second such meeting at the Copper Top.
Most of the table ordered various skillets; a few ordered omelets; I opted for two scrambled eggs with turkey sausage.
The place is on top of coffee refills; there was a gentleman circling the dining area, constantly refilling our coffee mugs and water glasses.
The food came out in a reasonable amount of time; the scrambled eggs featured a strong butter flavor.
The turkey sausage was heavy on the fennel and quite dry.
I'm told the skillets were "good," the meat-lovers omelet was "great" and the pancakes were "outstanding" - they certainly looked good, with their nice sear.
Total bill for the 8 of us was $70 - more than reasonable.
There are definitely better options available, but if you're in the neighborhood and hankerin' for some classic diner fare, it's worth a go.
